author: HBO Max
description:
Join hosts Frankey Smith and Tyler Coates, with Comics Correspondent Coy Jandreau, for an emotional and insightful deep dive into the highly anticipated Superman film from DC Studios. Special guests Greg Alba of The Reel Rejects and Brandon Davis of Phase Hero share their first reactions to David Corenswet’s perfromance as Superman, Nicholas Hoult’s Lex Luthor and their overall feelings around the film’s themes and tone. The roundtable explores the film’s central themes of hope, family, identity, and legacy, with breakdowns of the most powerful scenes, cast performances, character chemistry, and how this movie reshapes the future of the DC Universe (DCU). 

Perfect for fans of Superman, DC Comics, and superhero cinema, this episode brings together some of the most trusted voices in fandom for a thoughtful discussion on what makes Superman (2025) a defining moment for comic book films. description:
Executive producers Michael Patrick King, Julie Rottenberg, and Elisa Zuritsky, along with co-executive producer Samantha Irby and executive story editor Rachel Palmer, come together to dissect Aidan’s surprise visit. The episode opens on a light, fairytale note– including a playful homage to Sex and the City in Carrie’s closet– but reality quickly creeps in. The writers also delve into the all-too-real (but still funny!) challenges with Harry’s recovery, Charlotte’s vertigo, and LTW’s mounting stress about her editor.
